# Testing Guidelines

## Framework
This project uses **{{testFramework}}** for testing.

{{> testCommands }}

## Unit Tests
- Co-locate unit tests with the code they are testing (e.g. `user.service.spec.ts` next to `user.service.ts`).
{{#if isNestJS}}
- Use NestJS `TestBed` to create isolated testing modules.
- Mock all repository and external service dependencies using standard `jest.mock()` or custom mock providers in the TestBed.
{{else if isExpress}}
- Use a mock HTTP `req` and `res` object when testing controllers directly.
{{else if isFastify}}
- Use `fastify.inject()` to test route handlers without listening on a port.
{{else if isHono}}
- Use Hono's `app.request()` for lightweight integration & unit testing.
{{/if}}

## E2E Tests
- Place e2e tests in the `test/` directory at the project root.
- E2E tests should spin up the full application and hit a real (test-specific) database.
- Clear the database between test runs using a teardown script or `beforeEach` hook.

## Mocking Conventions
- Only mock external boundaries (databases, 3rd party APIs, queues).
- Do not over-mock internal business logic if testing it all together is fast and deterministic.

## JSDoc and Documentation
- Clearly comment complex test setups.
- Use the `Arrange, Act, Assert` pattern in every test block.
